modules.description: Provides functions to analyze and rewrite record update expressions, optimizing them by eliminating redundant assignments. Works with OCaml's abstract syntax trees and record types, focusing on fields that remain unchanged. Used to streamline performance-critical code where repeated record copies are common.

Provides functions to generate test expressions and record constructors from a list of field-value pairs, using OCaml AST structures. Operates on location-aware long identifiers and parsetree expressions to manipulate and extend record types. Used to dynamically construct test cases and update record fields in macro-generated code.
